OL,3,CReview into care campus reveals
OL,4,Csafeguarding failures after woman, 60,
OL,5,Cdies
OL,7,F"I am pleased to see that the
OL,8,Forganisations involved were open to
OL,9,Fthese improvements and lessons have
OL,10,Fbeen learned with many changes having
OL,11,Falready been implemented. I will now
OL,12,Fwork with SSAB partners to ensure that
OL,13,Fthis learning becomes normal practice."
OL,15,FThe National Autistic Society said in
OL,16,Fa statement: "Hazel's death was a
OL,17,Ftragedy and an unimaginable loss for
OL,18,Fher family. Our thoughts and
OL,19,Fsympathies continue to be with them.
